\mt1 1 Thessalonians
\is1 Introduction
\ip The Tisalunika the iney siyudad of prubinsya of Masidunya sakup of nasud of Ruma. Migpanulu si Paul of lalag of God there to Tisalunika of peg-awe din e there to Pilipus (Me Himu 17:1-4). Te ware naluhey, due me pegsupak from Jews neenenduenan of preaching of Paul there to non-Jews (Me Himu 17:5-9). Ne dutu, napehes si Paul eg-awe there to Tisalunika and miggendiye sikandin of Birya (Me Himu 17:10-13). Te ware naluhey, miggendiyad e again sikandin of Atinas (Me Himu 17:14-15). Nataman, migpabulus e sikandin there to Kurintu (Me Himu 18:1-17). Te arrival rin there, nakarawat sikandin of story of Timutiyu duma rin of work. Impangguhuran sikandin of Timutiyu concerning the egkeulaula of group of believers there to Tisalunika.
\ip This the \bk First letter of Paul of Matig-Tisalunika\bk*, wrote din in order to pegbagget and of peglig‑en of believers there. Migpasalamat sikandin of story concerning the faith ran and of love ran. Impasuman-suman din also sikandan concerning the living din impapitew rin kandan of there pad sikandin kandan. Intabak din again the me inse from there to believers concerning the return of the messiah, and ke egpakaangken naan ded of umul ware egtamanan the nammatey e believers of not pad eglibed the Messiah. Inggamit of Paul the this letter in order to pegpangguhud kandan of it's necessary continue sikandan eggimu of aldew-aldew work ran taheed of egtetahad sikandan of return of the messiah.
\iot Main components of Paul's letter
\io1 Introduction \ior 1:1\ior*
\io1 The thanking and praising \ior 1:2–2:16\ior*
